deck: Optimus Prime is revived as a zombie by Quintessons.
description: Fleeing through space from pursuing Decepticons, the Autobots dock at a mausoleum, the burial place of Autobots killed in the Great War. Daniel sees Optimus Prime alive - but how can this be? And though Optimus Prime can't remember the recent past, Rodimus Prime returns the Matrix to its former bearer, possibly spelling doom for all the Autobots.
name: Dark Awakening

deck: Daniel and Wheelie's first team-up! Oh noes!
description: Witnessing Ultra Magnus' bravery and selflessness during battle, Daniel and Wheelie decide to look up the commander's birthday and throw him a surprise party. THeir search brings them to a drifting Autobot storage asteroid, but trouble follows in the form of Cyclonus, Scourge, and the Sweeps. Cyclonus captures the two youths and sets the storage asteroid on a collision course with Cybertron.
name: Surprise Party

deck: A quick stroll through Cybertron leads Daniel Witwicky and Grimlock to someplace different.
description: On Cybertron Daniel is bored and walks away from a Peace Summit officiated by the Autobots. Along with Grimlock, the youyth finds an ancient chamber once used by the Quintessons to banish criminals to faraway dimensions. Grimlock accidentally activates the chamber and the two find themselves transported to a world called Minonia, where two wizards have been engaging in a power struggle for millennia.
name: Madman's Paradise

deck: In an attempt to cure Galvatron's madness, Cyclonus takes him to the medical planet Torkulon.
description: Swindle, Motormaster, and Laserbeak present Cyclonus with an ultimatum: Galvatron's rage must be tempered or the Decepticons will revolt. Seeing an opportunity to remove a wildcard from the equation, a crafty Quintesson tells Cyclonus of a planet called Torgulon, where mentally unstable individuals may go for treatment. Now Cyclonus must somehow trick his leader into travelling to this planet.
name: Webworld

deck: Several Autobots and Decepticons battle over a planet whose civilization revolves around music and whose inhabitants can use sound as a powerful weapon.
description: A strange and powerful sonic weapon cuts through space and destroys a huge comet, attracting the attention of both the Autobots and Decpticons. They trace the source of the weapon to a sound-based culture of harmonics on a nearby planet. The weapon itself is created from the combined singing of three citizens, and Galvatron quickly realizes he and Soundwave, can harness this weapon for the Decepticons if only they can record all three of its components.
name: Carnage in C-Minor

deck: In an attempt to alter history, the Quintessons open a Time Window to Cybertron's ancient past, but their meddling ultimately causes time itself to begin unraveling.
description: Detecting unusual Chronal Energy patterns emanating from an asteroid field, Perceptor, Blaster, Blurr and Wreck-Gar discover a Quintesson scientist activating a strange device. This device, the Time Window, offers a portal to the Cybertron of 11 million years ago - but before the Autobots can stop this mystery scheme, they mistakenly pass through the Window and A-3, a disoriented and distrustful Autobot appears. Will A-3's disappearance from the past spell doom for the Autobot's future?
name: Forever Is a Long Time Coming

deck: Set on regaining a physical body, the ghost of Starscream possesses Scourge and makes a deal with the devil.
description: Having taken over the body of Scourge, Starscream heads towards Cybertron's new moon, the disembodied head of Unicron. Within the head, Starscream reactivates the Chaos Bringer's brain functions, and the two strike a bargain: Unicron will remake Starscream's corporeal form in exchange for performing three labors, beginning with the theft of Metroplex's optic sensors from Autobot City on Earth.
name: Ghost in the Machine

deck: A recurring nightmare of Daniel's turns out to be an experiment by the Quintessons.
description: In his nightmares, Daniel is pursued by a gigantic Galvatron. The boy tells Rodimus Prime, who reassures him that they are only dreams no matter how real they seem. But the Quintessons have a machine that can look into the human youth's mind, and use those same dreams against the Autobots.
name: Nightmare Planet

Back to Zero! Earnest Wishes for Luffy!

deck: The Autobots discover that Dark Energon is responsible for an epidemic of natural disasters.
name: One Shall Rise Part 1
She Loves Sweets! Big Mam of the Four Emperors!

deck: While Galvatron threatens the Autobots with a vague and mysterious "ultimate weapon", First Aid leaves the Autobots.
description: First Aid's confidence is at an all-time low. The pacifist medic sees all the violence the humans perpetrate against each other, and is helpless to protect teammate Blades from injury during a Decepticon attack. Retreating from that same attack, Galvatron taunts Rodimus Prime with the threat of an Ultimate Weapon that will destroy the Autobots. When Swindle infiltrates Metroplex and easily bests First Aid, the forlorn Protectobot quits the Autobots and leaves behind the war.
name: The Ultimate Weapon
Many Problems Lie Ahead! A Trap Awaiting in the New World!
Finally Time to Go! Goodbye, Fish-Man Island!
To the New World! Heading for the Ultimate Sea!

deck: The Autobots team up with a surprising ally to save the Earth.
name: One Shall Rise Part 2
Here Comes Sabo! The Boy at the Gray Terminal!
I Won't Run! Ace's Desperate Rescue Operation!

deck: Attempting to retrieve their lost records journal, the Quintessons use subliminal messages on the Junkions, and inadvertently the entire galaxy.
description: On the planet of Junk, the Quintessons have located one of their lost journals. Unable to retrieve it due to the Junkions' interference, the five-faced villains use subliminal messages to brinwash the Autbot trash collectors into retrieving the Journal. The messages turn the Junkions xenophobic, and are rebroadcast through space as well, turning populations across the galaxy warlike.
name: The Big Broadcast of 2006
To The Sea Someday! The Pledge of the Three Brats!
Leaving the Dadan Family for Good?! The Kids' Hideout Has Been Built!
Luffy Becoming an Apprentice?! A Man Who Fought Against the King of the Pirates!

deck: A Quintesson device may just be the key to peace between two worlds.
description: Two warring planets, Zytoxis and Lynark, are in peace talks with the Autobots acting as mediators. Elsewhere, Perceptor locates the missing Quintesson Journal in the Angalic Sector, and attempts to retrieve it, but Predaking is headed there too. The Journal changes hands, moving from Autobots to Quintessons, and finally to the Decepticons. The journal is opened, revealing that it may hold the key to solving the conflict between Zytoxis and Lynark.
name: The Quintesson Journal
Reunited with Dark King Rayleigh! Decision Time for Luffy!
Back to Our Captain! A Jail Break at the Sky Island and the Incident on the Winter Island!
Encounter! The Great Swordsman Mihawk! Zoro's Self-Willed Deadly Struggle!
A Disaster for Sanji! The Queen's Return to the Kingdom!
Unexpected Relanding! Luffy, to Marineford!

deck: The return of the daleks but it also WW2
name: Victory of the Daleks

deck: Octane steals Trypticon in an attempt to use him to control the Decepticons.
description: Octane is on the run from Galvatron and wants leadership of the Decepticons for himself. He convinces Trypticon to head to the oil-producing nation of Carbomya, where they can consume all the ENergon they want in exchange for performing an occasional task for the country's sovereign, Abdul Fakhaddi. But Fakhaddi doesn't stop there and orders his new metal mobsters to steal numerous national monuments including the Taj Mahal, the Eiffel Tower, and the Kremlin.
name: Thief in the Night

deck: On the run from the Decepticons, Octane seeks asylum on Cybertron, where he encounters the ghost of Starscream, who is still scheming in death.
description: Cast out of the Decepticons, Octane forms an uneasy alliance with Autobot Sandstorm after discovering Galvatron has placed a bounty on the traitor's head. While fleeing from Scourge and the Sweeps, Octane hides in the Decepticon crypt on Cybertron and there encounters the unthinkable: the ghost of Starscream! This more notorious traitor offers to help Octane in exchange for revenge on Galvatron. Upon acceptance of his offer, Starsream's first action is to take over Octane's body!
name: Starscream's Ghost

deck: Jack comes in contact with a tribe of creatures who utilize their technology to subdue a group of supposedly savage beasts called "Woolies." Little does Jack know, there is more to the situation than meets the eye.
name: Jack, the Woolies, and the Chritchellites

deck: Samurai Jack befriends a group of scientists building a spaceship to escape Aku's tyrannical rule. Jack agrees to assist in their escape by fighting off the blockade orbiting the planet in return for a trip through time back to his home.
name: Jack in Space

deck: Jack searches for the magical jewel the Woolies told him would be able to send him back in time. Locating the last survivor of the race who can reveal it's location, Jack learns of how to find the jewel, and meets up with a woman questing for the same jewel. They journey through the desert together, but will they be able to share the jewel if they find it?
name: Jack and the Warrior Woman

deck: Samurai Jack hears of a mysterious island which possesses a well that can grant any wish. He arrives at the island and discovers the well is not alone.
name: Jack and the Three Blind

deck: Aku places a bounty on Jack's head, but is disappointed by the failure of some inept hunters, so he creates an evil spirit-clone version of Jack to finish our hero off for good.
name: Jack versus Mad Jack

deck: Jack seeks out a race of amphibians that possess a time machine capable of sending him back to his own time.
name: Jack Under the Sea

deck: Called on by a mysterious voice, Jack overcomes many obstacles and booby traps to find who is calling him. Deep in the earth he finds it is a creature made from rock and lava, who immediately challenges Jack to a fight, but why did it call for Jack?
name: Jack and the Lava Monster

deck: Jack finds himself opposed by The Scotsman, an opponent every bit as skilled as himself.
name: Jack and the Scotsman

deck: Jack joins a group of gangsters who work for Aku. He also agrees to help steal the heavily protected crystal that can give Aku power over the whole planet. Fortunately Jack has not become a traitor, but has his own plans of how to hand over the swag.
name: Jack And The Gangsters

deck: Aku tells fairy tales to children to make himself the hero and undermine the legend of Samurai Jack.
name: Aku's Fairy Tales

deck: Jack tries to save a peaceful tribe that move constantly due to an opposing food-stealing tribe of gorillas, in return for learning to "jump good."
name: Jack Learns to Jump Good

deck: Three "short stories": 1) Jack confronts a two-headed riddling worm who will grant him his wish if he can answer their questions. 2) Jack confronts a family that feed on metal, only for him and they to find out that they are robots. 3) Jack tries to rescue a wish-granting fairy from a gargoyle.
name: Jack Tales

deck: Edward and Alphonse Elric are delayed on their mission when they're ordered to help the military take down a rogue, known as the Freezing Alchemist.
description:
Japanese title: Hagane no Renkinjutsushi ()

The Elric brothers adjust to military life and take part in a manhunt for the dangerous Isaac the Freezer, a former State Alchemist bent on bringing Fuhrer Bradley down.
name: Fullmetal Alchemist

deck: While the Elric brothers continue on their trip to Reole, they remember what happened to them ten years ago - and how Ed became a State Alchemist.
description:
Japanese title: Hajimari no Hi ()

A glimpse into the past reveals the pain and desperation that drove the Elric boys to break alchemys greatest taboo - human transmutation - and their reasons for becoming dogs of the military.
name: The First Day

deck: The Elric brothers finally arrive in Reole, which they find is being manipulated by a false prophet.
description:
Japanese title: Jaky no Machi ()

Science and faith collide when the Elrics confront Father Cornello. He claims to work miracles, but the brothers suspect he is abusing a Philosophers Stone to manipulate his flock.
name: City of Heresy

deck: When Ed returns to Central City, he takes a particular interest in the study of Chimeras. Colonel Mustang decides to reward Edward for his actions in Reole by introducing him to an expert on the subject - Shou Tucker, known as the Sewing Life Alchemist.
description:
Japanese title: Renkinjutsushi no Kun ()

The Elrics meet Shou Tucker, a leading researcher in the field of chimeras. He has much to teach Ed and Al about alchemy - and the horrible cruelty that sometimes accompanies it.
name: An Alchemist's Anquish

deck: Recovering from the previous battle, Issei is focused on rescuing Asia by getting stronger. Though Rias once again berates him for him for attempting to rescue Asia as the two are of opposing sides. Issei heads to the park to practice chin-ups to get stronger and encounters Asia and they end up going on a date.
description:
Episode 4: "I'm Saving my Friend!

Recovering from the previous battle, Issei is focused on rescuing Asia by getting stronger. Though Rias once again berates him for him for attempting to rescue Asia as the two are of opposing sides. Issei heads to the park to practice chin-ups to get stronger and encounters Asia and they end up going on a date. Towards the end of the date, Raynare, the Fallen Angel who disguised herself as "Yuuma" in the first episode, appears and starts a fight with Issei, easily defeating the inexperienced Issei. Asia agrees to go with Raynare in exchange for Issei to be spared. Issei returns to the clubroom to try and get help and indirectly, Rias helps him after explaining that as a Pawn he can rank up to any other piece except for King. Kiba and Koneko go with him to the Church to save Asia while Rias and Akeno distract a number of Fallen Angels who were guarding the Church. Freed appears to stop Issei and his group but ends up defeated after Issei ranks up to Rook. After Freed escapes, Issei and his group head to the basement, witnessing the final moments of Raynare stealing Asia's Sacred Gear, killing her in the process.

Featured Characters

Devils:

  • Hyoudou Issei
  • Rias Gremory
  • Akeno Himejima
  • Koneko Toujou
  • Yuuto Kiba

Fallen Angels:

  • Raynare
  • Dohnaseek
  • Kalawarner
  • Mittelt

Humans:

  • Asia Argento
  • Freed Sellzen
name: I'm Saving My Friend!

deck: A vast array of worthy fighters besieged the elimination hall. Among them Goku, Krillin and Yamcha are paired off into different blocks to compete against other fighters in other to secure one of only eighth places in the tournament proper.
description: Original Title: ? (Deru ka!? Shugyou no Iryoku)
name: Elimination Round
